from @jan_krizaj - - MA PUNCH - 🥛🍵🍋

I’ve never been a big fan of milk punches as the milk and citrus wash out the complexity of alcohol in the drink and they are usually too intense in sweet and sour taste because you have to balance the filtered product (which is quite sour if you use lemon to curdle the milk) in order to get the final drink right. At the end you are left with very smooth drink which has less complexity and is probably too easy to drink.

So I made a drink using minimal quantity of lemon juice in order to preserve as much complexity through clarification.

I had three ingredients in my mind that I wanted to pair matcha, almonds and burned lemon.

I infused the gin with burned lemon peel (I threw lemon peels in the oven and burned the shit out of them, not like completely as they had still some yellow spots in the middle, everything else was black) then filtered and mixed with matcha tea, a touch of lemon and clarified through almond milk. The end result was balanced with a touch of sugar and 2,5ml of almond liqueur. Stirred and served.

The result - super creamy and complex drink with green and fresh matcha notes, you get the dark rich charred lemon and sort of like milky vanilla almonds.
